          If you somehow find a way to pass all these tests, you will (probably, I haven't decided how yet) be rewarded accordingly.
        </p>
        <p>
          Below, you will notice that there is a calendar enumerating all the days between June 1, 2023 and June 14, 2023.
          It should be noted, however, that this is no ordinary calendar. No, no, no. This is an ~advent~ calendar.
          Don't worry, though. I have been informed that even the smallest advent calendar can leave you shaking in your boots.
          Hence, I have added some extra protection for both of our sakes - you can only continue to the next day of the calendar under two conditions:<br>
          &emsp;&emsp;1. You have successfully completed the previous challenge and submitted the code, and<br>
          &emsp;&emsp;2. It has passed 12 am (EST) on the given day. <br>
        </p>
        <p>
          *Remember how I said that I should "get started" on your birthday present in Waterton Lakes? Yeah, I lied. I started after spring break. <br/>
